  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "With an endorsement of equal\nsuffrage Wednesday by the state\ngrange at Pullman and again yes\nterday by the Farmers union at\nOccur d'Alene, the woman suffrag-\nlists of Spokane feel highly elated\ntoday. At Pullman the cause was\npresented by committee consist\ning Of Mrs. A. E. House, Mrs. Bel\nDer, Mrs. A. P. Fassett, Mrs. Hutton\nand r. B. Martin. At Occur d'Alene\nthe issue was urged by a committee\nconsisting of Mrs. Gleason, Mrs.\nStafford, Mrs. D. c. Coates, Mrs.\nHutton and R. B. Martin. Both trips\nwere made in the private automo-\nbile of Mrs. Hutton."
    }
  ]
